editorialSummary.text: Stylish Greek restaurant serving fresh seafood in a Mediterranean-style whitewashed setting.

originalText.text: We had a Team dinner here in Hudson Yards Milo’s, place is very well maintained and run. It has good menu options and can get overwhelming for the waiting staff as some of our orders were getting fulfilled late but overall it’s a worth an experience. Being a vegetarian I had limited options but the hostess substituted a vegetarian pasta. Starters / appetizers were very good and deserts  especially the chocolate cake is a must try !! Definitely worth a visit

originalText.text:
Just walking into this restaurant makes you feel like a million bucks! A great place to take out clients, especially a few of them at once. Or even a special date

Get to walk up a chic, sexy staircase to the host desk of the restaurant. The white table cloths immediately signal to anyone this is ‘serious business’ ie fine dining

All the seafood was fresh, tasted delicious! While everyone recommends the fish, if you like lamb, the lamb chops are worth trying

Cocktails were made well, everybody enjoyed their

A lot of your experience hinges on how good/invested your server is! Ours started off a bit cranky, rough on the edges.. but eventually warmed up which changed our overall experience significantly

The fish bar / market inside is cool. Fun mini activity to check it out after you’ve ordered (so you can kill time while they prepare your food). Got to do this while hosting clients and they loved it

They have special lunch for $45.00 Monday to Friday included: appetizer,  main dish and dessert. Delicious food,  good service, nice view.
Delicious Greek cuisine and you should not miss it when you visit New York City  and Hudson Yards.
It's worth it and I recommend the place

originalText.text:
Milos New York, nestled in the heart of the city’s vibrant streets, offers a greek taste but falls short of delivering a truly satisfying dining experience.

One of the glaring issues plaguing Milos New York is its sluggish service. During my recent visit, I found myself waiting longer than anticipated for both a table and my order to be taken. While the bustling atmosphere adds to the restaurant’s charm, it unfortunately comes at the cost of efficiency, leaving diners feeling impatient and neglected. It took them so long to bring my Bourbon!! Had to remind them multiple times.

Moreover, the noise level at Milos New York borders on overwhelming. The cacophony of conversations makes it difficult to engage in meaningful conversation or simply enjoy a meal in peace. For those seeking a quiet dining experience, Milos New York may not be the ideal destination.

originalText.text: One of the best restaurants I’ve eaten at with everything from the fried zucchini stack, Mediterranean salad, Caesar salad, to the fish, lamb, and crab cake being delicious. We got a spot by the window and were able to see the sunset behind the vessel. I will say that parking is a little steep and the restaurant is a distance from the valet. I’d also like to mention that the chefs are nice enough to take you over to pick the fish you want to eat that night and will serve you at your table to give dinner and interact feel.
